44Ac 3:3 When he saw that Peter and John were about to go into the temple, he asked them to give him something.2
44Ac 3:4 Peter, along with John, looked him straight in the eye and said, "Look at us!"
44Ac 3:5 So the man watched them closely, expecting to get something from them.
44Ac 3:6 However, Peter said, "I don't have any silver or gold, but I'll give you what I do have. In the name of Jesus the Messiah from Nazareth, walk!"
44Ac 3:7 Then Peter took hold of his right hand and began to help him up. Immediately his feet and ankles became strong,
44Ac 3:8 and he sprang to his feet, stood up, and began to walk. Then he went with them into the temple, walking, jumping, and praising God. 
44Ac 3:9 When all the people saw him walking and praising God,
