45Rm 14:18 For the person who serves the Messiah in this way is pleasing to God and approved by people.
45Rm 14:19 Therefore, let's keep on pursuing those things that bring peace and that lead to building up one another.
45Rm 14:20 Do not destroy God's action for the sake of food. Everything is clean, but it is wrong to make another person stumble because of what you eat.
45Rm 14:21 The right thing to do is to avoid eating meat, drinking wine, or doing anything else that makes your brother stumble, upset, or weak.
45Rm 14:22 As for the faith you do have, have it as your own conviction before God. How blessed is the person who has no reason to condemn himself because of what he approves!
45Rm 14:23 But the person who has doubts is condemned if he eats, because he does not act in faith; and anything that is not done in faith is sin.1421
45Rm 15:1 Now we who are strong ought to be patient with the weaknesses of those who are not strong and must stop pleasing ourselves.
45Rm 15:2 Each of us must please our neighbor for the good purpose of building him up.
45Rm 15:3 For even the Messiah did not please himself. Instead, as it is written, "The insults of those who insult you have fallen on me."
45Rm 15:4 For everything that was written long ago was written to instruct us, so that we might have hope through the endurance and encouragement that the Scriptures give us.
45Rm 15:5 Now may God, the source of endurance and encouragement, allow you to live in harmony with each other as you follow the Messiah Jesus,
45Rm 15:6 so that with one mind and one voice you might glorify the God and Father of our Lord Jesus, the Messiah. 
45Rm 15:7 Therefore, accept one another, just as the Messiah accepted you, for the glory of God.
45Rm 15:8 For I tell you that the Messiah became a servant of the circumcised on behalf of God's truth in order to confirm the promises given to our ancestors,
45Rm 15:9 so that the gentiles may glorify God for his mercy. As it is written, "That is why I will praise you among the gentiles; I will sing praises to your name."
45Rm 15:10 Again he says, "Rejoice, you gentiles, with his people!"
45Rm 15:11 And again, "Praise the Lord, all you gentiles! Let all the nations praise him."
45Rm 15:12 And again, Isaiah says, "There will be a Root from Jesse. He will rise up to rule the gentiles, and the gentiles will hope in him."
45Rm 15:13 Now may God, the source of hope, fill you with all joy and peace as you believe, so that you may overflow with hope by the power of the Holy Spirit. 
45Rm 15:14 I myself am convinced, my brothers, that you yourselves are filled with goodness and full of all the knowledge you need to be able to instruct each other.
45Rm 15:15 However, on some points I have written to you rather boldly, both as a reminder to you and because of the grace given me by God
45Rm 15:16 to be a minister of the Messiah Jesus to the gentiles in the priestly service of the gospel of God, so that the offering brought by gentiles may be acceptable, sanctified by the Holy Spirit.
45Rm 15:17 Therefore, in the Messiah Jesus I have the right to boast about my work for God.
45Rm 15:18 For I am bold enough to tell you only about what the Messiah has accomplished through me in bringing gentiles to obedience. By my words and actions,
45Rm 15:19 by the power of signs and wonders, and by the power of God's Spirit, I have fully proclaimed the gospel of the Messiah from Jerusalem as far as Illyricum.
45Rm 15:20 My one ambition is to proclaim the gospel where the name of the Messiah is not known, so I don't build on someone else's foundation.
45Rm 15:21 Rather, as it is written, "Those who were never told about him will see, and those who have never heard will understand."
45Rm 15:22 This is why I have so often been hindered from to you.
45Rm 15:23 But now, having no further opportunities in these regions, I want to come to you, as I've desired to do for many years.
45Rm 15:24 Now that I am on my way to Spain, I hope to see you when I come your way and, after I have enjoyed your company for a while, to be sent on by you.23 
45Rm 15:25 Right now, however, I'm going to Jerusalem to minister to the saints,
45Rm 15:26 because the believers in Macedonia and Achaia have been eager to share their resources with the poor among the saints in Jerusalem.
45Rm 15:27 Yes, they were eager to do this, and in fact they are obligated to help them, for if the gentiles have shared in their spiritual blessings, they are obligated to be of service to them in material things. 
45Rm 15:28 So when I have completed this task and have put my seal on this contribution of theirs, I will visit you on my way to Spain.
45Rm 15:29 And I know that when I come to you I will come with the full blessing of the Messiah.
45Rm 15:30 Now I urge you, brothers, by our Lord Jesus, the Messiah, and by the love that the Spirit produces, to join me in my struggle, earnestly praying to God for me
45Rm 15:31 that I may be rescued from the unbelievers in Judea, that my ministry to Jerusalem may be acceptable to the saints,
45Rm 15:32 and that if it's God' will, I may come to you with joy and be refreshed together with you.
45Rm 15:33 Now may the God who grants peace be with all of you! Amen. 
45Rm 16:1 Now I commend to you our sister Phoebe, a servant in the church at Cenchraea.
