45Rm 16:21 Timothy, my fellow worker, greets you, as do Lucius, Jason, and Sosipater, my fellow Jews.
45Rm 16:22 I, Tertius, who penned this letter, greet you in the Lord.
45Rm 16:23 Gaius, who is host to me and the whole church, greets you. Erastus, the city treasurer, and our brother Quartus greet you.
45Rm 16:24 May the grace of our Lord Jesus, the Messiah, be with all of you!
45Rm 16:25 Now to the one who is able to strengthen you with my gospel and the message that I preach about Jesus, the Messiah, by revealing the secret that was kept hidden from long ago
45Rm 16:26 but now has been made known through the prophets to all the gentiles, in keeping with the decree of the eternal God to bring them to the obedience that springs from faith - 
45Rm 16:27 to the only wise God, through Jesus the Messiah, be glory forever! Amen.
