461Co 7:33 But a married man is concerned about things of this world, that is, about how he can please his wife,
461Co 7:34 and so his attention is divided. An unmarried woman or virgin is concerned about the affairs of the Lord, so that she may be holy in body and spirit. But a married woman is concerned about the affairs of this world, that is, about how she can please her husband.
461Co 7:35 I'm saying this for your benefit, not to put a noose around your necks, but to promote good order and unhindered devotion to the Lord.
461Co 7:36 If a man thinks he is not behaving properly toward his virgin, and if his passion is so strong that he feels he ought to marry her, let him do what he wants; he isn't sinning. Let them get married.
461Co 7:37 However, if a man stands firm in his resolve, feels no necessity, and has made up his mind to keep her a virgin, he will be acting appropriately.
461Co 7:38 So then the man who marries the virgin acts appropriately, but the man who refrains from marriage does even better. 
461Co 7:39 A wife is bound to her husband as long as he lives. But if her husband dies, she is free to marry anyone she wishes, only in the Lord.
461Co 7:40 However, in my opinion she will be happier if she stays as she is. And in saying this, I think that I, too, have God's Spirit.
461Co 8:1 Now concerning food offered to idols£º We know that we all possess knowledge. Knowledge puffs up, but love builds up.
461Co 8:2 If anyone thinks he really knows something, he has not yet learned it as he ought to know it.
461Co 8:3 But anyone who loves God is known by him.
461Co 8:4 Now concerning eating food offered to idols£º We know that no idol is real in this world and that there is only one God.
461Co 8:5 For even if there are "gods" in heaven and on earth (as indeed there are many so-called "gods" and "lords"),
461Co 8:6 yet for us there is only one God, the Father, from whom everything came into being and for whom we live. And there is only one Lord, Jesus the Messiah, through whom everything came into being and through whom we live.
461Co 8:7 But not everyone has this knowledge. Some people are so accustomed to idolatry that when they eat food that has been offered to an idol, their conscience becomes contaminated because it is weak.
461Co 8:8 However, food will not bring us closer to God. We are no worse off if we do not eat food that has been offered to an idol, and no better off if we do. 
461Co 8:9 But you must see to it that this right of yours does not become a stumbling block for those who are weak.
461Co 8:10 For if anyone with a weak conscience sees you, who knows better, eating in an idol's temple, he will be encouraged to eat what has been offered to idols, won't he - 
461Co 8:11 In that case, the weak brother for whom the Messiah died is ruined by your knowledge.
461Co 8:12 When you sin against your brothers in this way and wound their weak consciences, you are sinning against the Messiah.
461Co 8:13 Therefore, if food that I eat causes my brother to stumble, I will never eat meat again, in order to keep my brother from stumbling.810
461Co 9:1 I am free, am I not? I am an apostle, am I not? I have seen Jesus our Lord, haven't I? You are the result of my work in the Lord, aren't you - 
461Co 9:2 If I am not an apostle to other people, surely I am one to you, for you are the evidence of my apostolic authority from the Lord.
461Co 9:3 This is my defense to those who would examine me£º
461Co 9:4 We have the right to earn our food, don't we - 
461Co 9:5 We have the right to take a believing wife with us like the other apostles, the Lord's brothers, and Cephas, don't we - 
461Co 9:6 Or is it only Barnabas and I who have to keep on working for a living - 
461Co 9:7 Who ever goes to war at his own expense? Who plants a vineyard and does not eat any of its grapes? Or who takes care of a flock and does not drink any of its milk - 
461Co 9:8 I am not saying this on human authority, am I? The law says the same thing, doesn't it - 
461Co 9:9 For in the law of Moses it is written, "You must not muzzle an ox while it is treading out the grain." God is not only concerned about oxen, is he - 
461Co 9:10 Isn't he really speaking for our benefit? Yes, this was written for our benefit, because the one who plows should plow in hope, and the one who threshes should thresh in hope of sharing in the crop.
461Co 9:11 If we have sown spiritual seed among you, is it too much if we reap material benefits from you - 
461Co 9:12 If others enjoy this right over you, don't we have a stronger claim? But we did not use this right. On the contrary, we tolerate everything in order not to put an obstacle in the way of the gospel of the Messiah. 
461Co 9:13 You know that those who work in the temple get their food from the temple and that those who serve at the altar get their share of its offerings, don't you - 
461Co 9:14 In the same way, the Lord has ordered that those who proclaim the gospel should make their living from the gospel.9
461Co 9:15 But I have not used any of these rights, and I'm not writing this so that they may be applied in my case. I would rather die than let anyone deprive me of my reason for boasting.
461Co 9:16 For if I preach the gospel, I have nothing to boast about, for this obligation has been entrusted to me. How terrible it would be for me if I didn't preach the gospel!
461Co 9:17 For if I preach voluntarily, I get a reward, but if I am unwilling to do it, I am still entrusted with that obligation.
461Co 9:18 What, then, is my reward? It is to be able to preach the gospel free of charge, and so I never resort to demanding my rights when I'm preaching the gospel.
461Co 9:19 Although I am free from everyone's expectations, I have made myself a servant to all of them to win more people.
461Co 9:20 To the Jews I became like a Jew in order to win Jews. To those under the law I became like a man under the law, in order to win those under the law (although I myself am not under the law).
461Co 9:21 To those who do not have the law, I became like a man who does not have the law in order to win those who do not have the law. However, I am not free from God's law, but I'm subject to the Messiah's law.
461Co 9:22 To the weak I became weak in order to win the weak. I have become all things to all people so that by all possible means I might save some of them.
461Co 9:23 I do all this for the sake of the gospel in order to have a share in its blessings.921
461Co 9:24 You know that in a race all the runners run but only one wins the prize, don't you? You must run in such a way that you may be victorious.
461Co 9:25 Everyone who enters an athletic contest practices self-control in everything. They do it to win a wreath that withers away, but we run to win a prize that never fades.
461Co 9:26 That is the way I run, with a clear goal in mind. That is the way I fight, not like someone shadow boxing.
461Co 9:27 No, I keep on disciplining my body, making it serve me so that after I have preached to others, I myself will not somehow be disqualified. 
461Co 10:1 Now I do not want you to be ignorant, brothers, of the fact that all of our ancestors who left Egypt were under the cloud. They all went through the sea,
461Co 10:2 and they all were immersed into Moses in the cloud and in the sea.
461Co 10:3 They all ate the same spiritual food
461Co 10:4 and drank the same spiritual drink, for they drank from the spiritual rock that went with them. That rock was the Messiah.
461Co 10:5 But God wasn't pleased with most of those people, and so they were struck down in the wilderness.4
461Co 10:6 Now their experiences serve as examples for us so that we won't set our hearts on evil as they did.
461Co 10:7 Let's stop being idolaters, as some of them were. As it is written, "The people sat down to eat and drink and got up to play."
461Co 10:8 Let's stop sinning sexually, as some of them were doing, and on a single day 23,000 fell dead.
461Co 10:9 Let's stop putting the Lord to the test, as some of them were doing, and were destroyed by snakes.
461Co 10:10 You must stop complaining, as some of them were doing, and were annihilated by the destroyer.
461Co 10:11 These things happened to them to serve as an example, and they were written down as a warning for us in whom the culmination of the ages has been attained.
461Co 10:12 Therefore, whoever thinks he is standing securely should watch out so he doesn't fall.
461Co 10:13 No temptation has overtaken you that is unusual for human beings. But God is faithful, and he will not allow you to be tempted beyond your strength. Instead, along with the temptation he will also provide a way out, so that you may be able to endure it. 
461Co 10:14 And so, my dear friends, keep on running away from idolatry.
461Co 10:15 I am talking to sensible people. Apply what I am saying to yourselves.
461Co 10:16 The cup of blessing that we bless is a sign of our sharing in the blood of the Messiah, isn't it? The bread that we break is a sign of our sharing in the body of the Messiah, isn't it - 
461Co 10:17 Because there is one loaf, we who are many are one body, because all of us eat from the same loaf. 
461Co 10:18 Look at the Israelites from a human point of view. Those who eat the sacrifices share in what is on the altar, don't they - 
461Co 10:19 Am I suggesting that an offering made to idols means anything, or that an idol itself means anything - 
461Co 10:20 Hardly! What they offer, they offer to demons and not to God, and I do not want you to become partners with demons.
461Co 10:21 You cannot drink the cup of the Lord and the cup of demons. You cannot dine with the Lord and dine with demons,
461Co 10:22 or you'll provoke the Lord to jealousy, won't you? Are we are stronger than he is? 
461Co 10:23 Everything is permissible, but not everything is helpful. Everything is permissible, but not everything builds up.
461Co 10:24 No one should seek his own welfare, but rather his neighbor's.10
461Co 10:25 Eat anything that is sold in the meat market without raising any question about it on the grounds of conscience,
461Co 10:26 for "the earth and everything in it belong to the Lord."
461Co 10:27 If an unbeliever invites you to his house and you wish to go, eat whatever is set before you, raising no question on the grounds of conscience.
461Co 10:28 However, if someone says to you, "This was offered as a sacrifice," don't eat it, both out of consideration for the one who told you and also for the sake of conscience.
461Co 10:29 I mean, of course, his conscience, not yours. For why should my freedom be determined by someone else's conscience - 
461Co 10:30 If I eat with thankfulness, why should I be denounced because of what I am thankful for - 2910
461Co 10:31 Therefore, whether you eat or drink, or whatever you do, do everything for the glory of God.
461Co 10:32 Don't become a stumbling block to Jews or Greeks or to the church of God,
461Co 10:33 just as I myself try to please everybody in every way. I don't look out for my own benefit, but rather for the benefit of many people, so that they might be saved.
461Co 11:1 Imitate me, as I do the Messiah.
461Co 11:2 I praise you for remembering everything I told you and for holding to the traditions that I passed on to you.
461Co 11:3 Now I want you to realize that the Messiah is the head of every man, and man is the head of the woman, and God is the head of the Messiah.
461Co 11:4 Every man who prays or prophesies with something on his head dishonors his head,
461Co 11:5 and every woman who prays or prophesies with her head uncovered dishonors her head, which is the same as having her head shaved.
461Co 11:6 So if a woman does not cover her head, she should cut off her hair. If it is a disgrace for a woman to cut off her hair or shave her head, let her cover her own head.3
461Co 11:7 A man should not cover his head, because he exists as God's image and glory. But the woman is man's glory.
461Co 11:8 For man did not come from woman, but woman from man;
461Co 11:9 and man was not created for woman, but woman for man.
461Co 11:10 This is why a woman should have authority over her own head£º because of the angels.
461Co 11:11 In the Lord, however, woman is not independent of man, nor is man of woman.
461Co 11:12 For as woman came from man, so man comes through woman. But everything comes from God.
461Co 11:13 Decide for yourselves£º Is it proper for a woman to pray to God with her head uncovered - 
461Co 11:14 Nature itself teaches you neither that it is disgraceful for a man to have long hair
461Co 11:15 nor that hair is a woman's glory, since hair is given as a substitute for coverings.
461Co 11:16 But if anyone wants to argue about this, we do not have any custom like this, nor do any of God's churches.
461Co 11:17 Now I am not praising you in giving you the following instructions. When you gather, it is not for the better but for the worse.
461Co 11:18 For in the first place, I hear that when you gather as a church there are divisions among you, and I partly believe it.
461Co 11:19 Of course, there must be factions among you to show which of you are genuine!1117
461Co 11:20 When you gather in the same place, it is not to eat the Lord's Supper.
461Co 11:21 For as you eat, each of you rushes to eat his own supper, and one person goes hungry while another gets drunk.
461Co 11:22 You have homes in which to eat and drink, don't you? Or do you despise God's church and humiliate those who have nothing? What should I say to you? Should I praise you? I will not praise you for this! 
461Co 11:23 For I received from the Lord what I also passed on to you - how the Lord Jesus, on the night he was betrayed, took a loaf of bread,
461Co 11:24 gave thanks for it, and broke it in pieces, saying, "This is my body that is for you. Keep doing this in memory of me."
461Co 11:25 He did the same with the cup after the supper, saying, "This cup is the new covenant in my blood. As often as you drink from it, keep doing this in memory of me."
461Co 11:26 For as often as you eat this bread and drink from this cup, you proclaim the Lord's death until he comes. 
461Co 11:27 Therefore, whoever eats the bread or drinks from the cup in an unworthy manner will be held responsible for the Lord's body and blood.
461Co 11:28 A person must examine himself and then eat the bread and drink from the cup,
461Co 11:29 because whoever eats and drinks without recognizing the body, eats and drinks judgment on himself.
461Co 11:30 That's why so many of you are weak and sick and a considerable number are dying.
461Co 11:31 But if we judged ourselves correctly, we would not be judged.
461Co 11:32 Now, while we are being judged by the Lord, we are being disciplined so we won't be condemned along with the world.
461Co 11:33 Therefore, my brothers, when you gather to eat, wait for each other.
461Co 11:34 If anyone is hungry, he should eat at home, so that when you gather it may not bring judgment on you. And when I come I will give instructions concerning the other matters.11
461Co 12:1 Now concerning spiritual gifts, brothers, I don't want you to be ignorant.
461Co 12:2 You know that when you were unbelievers, you were enticed and led astray to worship idols that couldn't even speak.
461Co 12:3 For this reason I want you to be aware that no one who is speaking by God's Spirit can say, "Jesus is cursed," and no one can say, "Jesus is Lord," except by the Holy Spirit. 
461Co 12:4 Now there are varieties of gifts, but the same Spirit,
461Co 12:5 and there are varieties of ministries, but the same Lord.
461Co 12:6 There are varieties of results, but it is the same God who produces all the results in everyone.
461Co 12:7 To each person has been given the ability to manifest the Spirit for the common good.
461Co 12:8 To one has been given a message of wisdom by the Spirit; to another the ability to speak with knowledge according to the same Spirit;
461Co 12:9 to another faith by the same Spirit; to another gifts of healing by that one Spirit;
461Co 12:10 to another miraculous results; to another prophecy; to another the ability to distinguish between spirits; to another various kinds of languages; and to another the interpretation of languages.
461Co 12:11 But one and the same Spirit produces all these results and gives what he wants to each person. 
461Co 12:12 For just as the body is one and yet has many parts, and all the parts of the body, though many, form a single body, so it is with the Messiah.
461Co 12:13 For by one Spirit all of us - Jews and Greeks, slaves and free - were baptized into one body and were all privileged to drink from one Spirit.12
461Co 12:14 For the body does not consist of only one part, but of many.
461Co 12:15 If the foot says, "Since I'm not a hand, I'm not part of the body," that does not make it any less a part of the body, does it - 
461Co 12:16 And if the ear says, "Since I'm not an eye, I'm not part of the body," that does not make it any less a part of the body, does it - 
461Co 12:17 If the whole body were an eye, where would the sense of hearing be? If the whole body were an ear, where would the sense of smell be - 
461Co 12:18 But now God has arranged the parts, every one of them, in the body according to his plan.
461Co 12:19 Now if all of it were one part, there wouldn't be a body, would there - 
461Co 12:20 So there are many parts, but one body.
461Co 12:21 The eye cannot say to the hand, "I don't need you," or the head to the feet, "I don't need you."
461Co 12:22 On the contrary, those parts of the body that seem to be weaker are in fact indispensable,
461Co 12:23 and the parts of the body that we think are less honorable are treated with special honor, and we make our less attractive parts more attractive.
461Co 12:24 However, our attractive parts don't need this. But God has put the body together and has given special honor to the parts that lack it,
461Co 12:25 so that there might be no disharmony in the body, but that its parts should have the same concern for each other.
461Co 12:26 If one part suffers, every part suffers with it. If one part is praised, every part rejoices with it.
461Co 12:27 Now you are the Messiah's body and individual parts of it.
461Co 12:28 God has appointed in the church first of all apostles, second prophets, third teachers, then those who perform miracles, those who have gifts of healing, those who help others, administrators, and those who speak various kinds of languages.
461Co 12:29 Not all are apostles, are they? Not all are prophets, are they? Not all are teachers, are they? Not all perform miracles, do they - 
461Co 12:30 Not all have the gift of healing, do they? Not all speak in other languages, do they? Not all interpret, do they - 
461Co 12:31 Keep on desiring the better gifts. And now I will show you the best way of all.1229
461Co 13:1 If I speak in the languages of humans and angels but have no love, I have become a reverberating gong or a clashing cymbal.
461Co 13:2 If I have the gift of prophecy and can understand all secrets and every form of knowledge, and if I have absolute faith so as to move mountains but have no love, I am nothing.
461Co 13:3 Even if I give away everything that I have and sacrifice myself, but have no love, I gain nothing.
461Co 13:4 Love is always patient; love is always kind; love is never envious or arrogant with pride. Nor is she conceited,
461Co 13:5 and she is never rude; she never thinks just of herself or ever gets annoyed. She never is resentful;
461Co 13:6 is never glad with sin; she's always glad to side with truth, and pleased that truth shall win.
461Co 13:7 She bears up under everything, believes the best in all, there is no limit to her hope, and she will never fall.
461Co 13:8 Love never fails. Now if there are prophecies, they will be done away with. If there are languages, they will cease. If there is knowledge, it will be done away with.
461Co 13:9 For what we know is incomplete and what we prophesy is incomplete.
461Co 13:10 But when what is complete comes, then what is incomplete will be done away with.
461Co 13:11 When I was a child, I spoke like a child, thought like a child, and reasoned like a child. When I became a man, I gave up my childish ways.
461Co 13:12 Now we see only an indistinct image in a mirror, but then we will be face to face. Now what I know is incomplete, but then I will know fully, even as I have been fully known. 
461Co 13:13 Right now three things remain£º faith, hope, and love. But the greatest of these is love.
461Co 14:1 Keep on pursuing love, and keep on desiring spiritual gifts, especially the ability to prophesy.
461Co 14:2 For the person who speaks in another language is not actually speaking to people but to God. Indeed, no one understands him, because he is talking about secrets by the Spirit.
461Co 14:3 But the person who prophesies speaks to people for their upbuilding, encouragement, and comfort.
461Co 14:4 The person who speaks in another language builds himself up, but the person who prophesies builds up the church.
461Co 14:5 Now I wish that all of you could speak in other languages, but especially that you could prophesy. The person who prophesies is more important than the person who speaks in another language, unless he interprets it so that the church may be built up.
461Co 14:6 Indeed, brothers, if I come to you speaking in other languages, what good will I be to you unless I speak to you in some revelation, knowledge, prophecy, or teaching - 
461Co 14:7 In the same way, lifeless instruments like the flute or harp produce sounds. But if there's no difference in the notes, how can a person tell what tune is being played - 
461Co 14:8 For example, if a bugle doesn't sound a clear call, who will get ready for battle - 
461Co 14:9 In the same way, unless you speak an intelligible message with your language, how will anyone know what is being said? You'll be talking into the air!
461Co 14:10 There are, I suppose, many different languages in the world, yet none of them is without meaning.
461Co 14:11 If I don't know the meaning of the language, I will be a foreigner to the speaker and the speaker will be a foreigner to me.
461Co 14:12 In the same way, since you're so desirous of spiritual gifts, you must keep on desiring them for the upbuilding of the church.
461Co 14:13 Therefore, the person who speaks in another language should pray for the ability to interpret it.
461Co 14:14 For if I pray in another language, my spirit prays but my mind is not productive.
461Co 14:15 What does this mean? I will pray with my spirit, but I will also pray with my mind. I will sing psalms with my spirit, but I will also sing psalms with my mind.
461Co 14:16 Otherwise, if you say a blessing with your spirit, how can an otherwise uneducated person say "Amen" to your thanksgiving, since he does not know what you're saying - 
461Co 14:17 It's good for you to give thanks, but it does not build up the other person.
461Co 14:18 I thank God that I speak in other languages more than all of you.
461Co 14:19 But in church I would rather speak five words with my mind to instruct others than 10,000 words in another language.
461Co 14:20 Brothers, stop being childish in your thinking. Be like infants with respect to evil, but think like adults.
461Co 14:21 In the law it is written, "By means of other languages and through the mouths of foreigners I will speak to this people, but even then they will not listen to me," declares the Lord.
461Co 14:22 Other languages, then, are meant to be a sign, not for believers, but for unbelievers, while prophecy is meant, not for unbelievers, but for believers.
461Co 14:23 Now if the whole church gathers in the same place and everyone is speaking in other languages, when uneducated people or unbelievers come in, they will say that you are out of your mind, won't they - 
461Co 14:24 But if everyone is prophesying, when an unbeliever or an uneducated person comes in he will be convicted and examined by everything that's happening.
461Co 14:25 His secret, inner heart will become known, and so he will bow down to the ground and worship God, declaring, "God is truly among you!"22
461Co 14:26 What, then, does this mean, brothers? When you gather, everyone has a psalm, teaching, revelation, other language, or interpretation. Everything must be done for upbuilding.
461Co 14:27 If anyone speaks in another language, only two or three at the most should do so, one at a time, and somebody must interpret.
461Co 14:28 If an interpreter is not present, the speaker should remain silent in the church and speak to himself and God.
461Co 14:29 Two or three prophets should speak, and others should weigh carefully what is said.
461Co 14:30 If a revelation is made to another person who is seated, the first person should be silent.
461Co 14:31 For everyone can prophesy in turn, so that everyone can be instructed and everyone can be encouraged.
461Co 14:32 The spirits of prophets are subject to the prophets,
461Co 14:33 for God is not a God of disorder but of peace. As in all the churches of the saints,
461Co 14:34 the women must keep silent in the churches. They are not allowed to speak out, but must place themselves in submission, as the oral law also says.
461Co 14:35 If they want to learn anything, they should ask their own husbands at home, for it is inappropriate for a woman to speak out in church.14
461Co 14:36 Did God's word originate with you? Are you the only people it has reached - 
461Co 14:37 If anyone thinks he is a prophet or a spiritual person, he must acknowledge that what I am writing to you is the Lord's command.
461Co 14:38 But if anyone ignores this, he should be ignored.
461Co 14:39 Therefore, my brothers, desire the ability to prophesy, and do not prevent others from speaking in other languages.
461Co 14:40 But everything must be done in a proper and orderly way. 
461Co 15:1 Now I'm making known to you, brothers, the gospel that I proclaimed to you, which you accepted, on which you have taken your stand,
461Co 15:2 and by which you are also being saved if you hold firmly to the message I proclaimed to you - unless, of course, your faith was worthless. 
461Co 15:3 For I passed on to you the most important points that I received£º The Messiah died for our sins according to the Scriptures,
461Co 15:4 he was buried, he was raised on the third day according to the Scriptures - and is still alive! - 
461Co 15:5 and he was seen by Cephas, and then by the twelve disciples.
461Co 15:6 After that, he was seen by more than 500 brothers at one time, most of whom are still alive, though some have died.
461Co 15:7 Next he was seen by James, then by all the apostles,
461Co 15:8 and finally he was seen by me, as though I were born abnormally late. 
461Co 15:9 For I am the least of the apostles and not even fit to be called an apostle because I persecuted God's church.
461Co 15:10 But by God's grace I am what I am, and his grace shown to me was not wasted. Instead, I worked harder than all the others - not I, of course, but God's grace that was with me.
461Co 15:11 So, whether it was I or the others, this is what we preach, and this is what you believed.9
461Co 15:12 Now if we preach that the Messiah has been raised from the dead, how can some of you keep claiming there is no resurrection of the dead - 
461Co 15:13 If there is no resurrection of the dead, then the Messiah has not been raised,
461Co 15:14 and if the Messiah has not been raised, then our message means nothing and your faith means nothing.
461Co 15:15 In addition, we are found to be false witnesses about God because we testified on God's behalf that he raised the Messiah - whom he did not raise if in fact it is true that the dead are not raised.
461Co 15:16 For if the dead are not raised, then the Messiah has not been raised,
461Co 15:17 and if the Messiah has not been raised, your faith is worthless and you are still imprisoned by your sins.
461Co 15:18 Yes, even those who have died believing in the Messiah are lost.
461Co 15:19 If we have set our hopes on the Messiah in this life only, we deserve more pity than any other people.12
461Co 15:20 But at this moment the Messiah stands risen from the dead, the first one offered in the harvest of those who have died.
461Co 15:21 For since death came through a man, the resurrection of the dead also came through a man.
461Co 15:22 For as in Adam all die, so also in the Messiah will all be made alive.
461Co 15:23 However, this will happen to each person in the proper order£º first the Messiah, then those who belong to the Messiah when he comes.
461Co 15:24 Then the end will come, when after he has done away with every ruler and every authority and power, the Messiah hands over the kingdom to God the Father.
461Co 15:25 For he must rule until God puts all the Messiah's enemies under his feet.
461Co 15:26 The last enemy to be done away with is death,
461Co 15:27 for "God has put everything under his feet." Now when he says, "Everything has been put under him," this clearly excludes the one who put everything under him.
461Co 15:28 But when everything has been put under him, then the Son himself will also become subject to the one who put everything under him, so that God may be all in all.
461Co 15:29 Otherwise, what will those people do who are being baptized because of those who have died? If the dead are not raised at all, why are they being baptized because of them - 
461Co 15:30 And why in fact are we being endangered every hour - 
461Co 15:31 I face death every day! That is as certain, brothers, as it is that I am proud of you in the Messiah, Jesus our Lord.
461Co 15:32 If I have fought with wild animals in Ephesus from merely human motives, what do I get out of it? If the dead are not raised, "Let's eat and drink, for tomorrow we die."
461Co 15:33 Stop being deceived£º "Wicked friends lead to evil ends."
461Co 15:34 Come back to your senses as you should, and stop sinning! For some of you - I say this to your shame - don't fully know God. 
461Co 15:35 But someone will ask, "How are the dead raised? What kind of body will they have when they come back?"
461Co 15:36 You fool! The seed you plant does not come to life unless it dies,
461Co 15:37 and what you plant is not the form that it will be, but a bare kernel, whether it is wheat or something else.
