49Eph 3:3 and how this secret was made known to me through a revelation, just as I wrote about briefly in the past.
49Eph 3:4 By reading this, you will be able to grasp my understanding of the secret about the Messiah,
49Eph 3:5 which in previous generations was not made known to human beings as it has now been revealed by the Spirit to God's holy apostles and prophets. This is that secret£º
49Eph 3:6 The gentiles are heirs-in-common, members-in-common of the body, and common participants in what was promised by the Messiah Jesus through the gospel.
49Eph 3:7 I have become a servant of this gospel according to the gift of God's grace that was given me by the working of his power.
49Eph 3:8 To me, the very least of all the saints, this grace was given so that I might proclaim to the gentiles the immeasurable wealth of the Messiah
