49Eph 4:1 I, therefore, the prisoner of the Lord, urge you to live in a way that is worthy of the calling to which you have been called,
49Eph 4:2 demonstrating all expressions of humility, gentleness, and patience, accepting one another in love.
49Eph 4:3 Do your best to maintain the unity of the Spirit by means of the bond of peace.
49Eph 4:4 There is one body and one Spirit. Likewise, you were called to the one hope of your calling.
49Eph 4:5 There is one Lord, one faith, one baptism,
49Eph 4:6 one God and Father of all, who is above all, through all, and in all. 
49Eph 4:7 Now to each one of us grace has been given proportionate to the measure of the Messiah's gift.
49Eph 4:8 That is why God says, "When he went up to the highest place he led captives into captivity and gave gifts to people."
49Eph 4:9 Now what does this "he went up" mean except that he also had gone down into the lower parts of the earth - 
49Eph 4:10 The one who went down is the same one who went up above all the heavens so that all things would be fulfilled.
