49Eph 4:13 until all of us are united in the faith and in the full knowledge of God's Son, and until we attain mature adulthood and the full standard of development in the Messiah.
49Eph 4:14 Then we will no longer be little children, tossed like waves and blown about by every wind of doctrine, by people's trickery, or by clever strategies that would lead us astray.
49Eph 4:15 Instead, by speaking the truth in love, we will grow up completely and become one with the head, that is, one with the Messiah,
49Eph 4:16 in whom the whole body is united and held together by every ligament with which it is supplied. As each individual part does its job, the body builds itself up in love.14
49Eph 4:17 Therefore, I tell you and insist on in the Lord not to live any longer like the gentiles live, thinking worthless thoughts.
49Eph 4:18 They are darkened in their understanding and separated from the life of God because of their ignorance and hardness of heart.
49Eph 4:19 Since they have lost all sense of shame, they have abandoned themselves to sensuality and practice every kind of sexual perversion without restraint.
49Eph 4:20 However, that is not the way you came to know the Messiah.
49Eph 4:21 Surely you have listened to him and have been taught by him, since truth is in Jesus.
49Eph 4:22 Regarding your former way of life, you were taught to strip off your old nature, which is being ruined by its deceptive desires,
49Eph 4:23 to be renewed in your mental attitude,
49Eph 4:24 and to clothe yourselves with the new nature, which was created according to God's image in righteousness and true holiness.
49Eph 4:25 Therefore, stripping off falsehood, "let each of us speak the truth to his neighbor," for we belong to one another.
49Eph 4:26 "Be angry, yet do not sin." Do not let the sun set while you are still angry,
49Eph 4:27 and do not give the devil an opportunity to work.
49Eph 4:28 The thief must no longer steal but must work hard and do what is good with his own hands, so that he might earn something to give to the needy.
49Eph 4:29 Let no filthy talk be heard from your mouths, but only what is good for building up people and meeting the need of the moment. This way you will administer grace to those who hear you.
49Eph 4:30 Do not grieve the Holy Spirit, by whom you were marked with a seal for the day of redemption.
49Eph 4:31 Let all bitterness, wrath, anger, quarreling, and slander be put away from you, along with all hatred.
49Eph 4:32 And be kind to one another, compassionate, forgiving one another just as God has forgiven you in the Messiah.429
49Eph 5:1 So be imitators of God, as his dear children.
49Eph 5:2 Live lovingly, just as the Messiah also loved us and gave himself for us as an offering and sacrifice, a fragrant aroma to God.
49Eph 5:3 Do not let sexual sin, impurity of any kind, or greed even be mentioned among you, as is proper for saints.
49Eph 5:4 Obscene, flippant, or vulgar talk is totally inappropriate. Instead, let there be thanksgiving.
49Eph 5:5 For you know very well that no immoral or impure person, or anyone who is greedy (that is, an idolater), has an inheritance in the kingdom of the Messiah and of God. 
49Eph 5:6 Do not let anyone deceive you with meaningless words, for it is because of these things that God becomes angry with those who disobey.
49Eph 5:7 So do not be partners with them.
49Eph 5:8 For once you were darkness, but now you are light in the Lord. Live as children of light,
49Eph 5:9 for the fruit that the light produces consists of every form of goodness, righteousness, and truth.
49Eph 5:10 Determine what pleases the Lord,
49Eph 5:11 and have nothing to do with the unfruitful actions that darkness produces. Instead, expose them for what they are.
49Eph 5:12 For it is shameful even to mention what is done by these disobedient people in secret.
49Eph 5:13 But everything that is exposed to the light becomes visible,
49Eph 5:14 for the light is making everything visible. That is why it says, "Wake up, sleeper! Arise from the dead, and the Messiah will shine on you.''
49Eph 5:15 So, then, be careful how you live. Do not be unwise but wise,
49Eph 5:16 making the best use of your time because the times are evil.
49Eph 5:17 Therefore, do not be foolish, but understand what the Lord's will is.
49Eph 5:18 Stop getting drunk with wine, which leads to wild living, but keep on being filled with the Spirit.
49Eph 5:19 Then you will recite to one another psalms, hymns, and spiritual songs; you will sing and make music to the Lord with your hearts;
49Eph 5:20 you will consistently give thanks to God the Father for everything in the name of our Lord Jesus, the Messiah;
49Eph 5:21 and you will submit to one another out of reverence for the Messiah.
49Eph 5:22 Wives, submit yourselves to your husbands as to the Lord.
49Eph 5:23 For the husband is the head of his wife as the Messiah is the head of the church. It is he who is the Savior of the body.
49Eph 5:24 Indeed, just as the church is submissive to the Messiah, so wives must be submissive to their husbands in everything. 
49Eph 5:25 Husbands, love your wives as the Messiah loved the church and gave himself for it,
49Eph 5:26 so that he might make it holy by cleansing it, washing it with water and the word,
49Eph 5:27 and might present the church to himself in all its glory, without a spot or wrinkle or anything of the kind, but holy and without fault.
49Eph 5:28 In the same way, husbands must love their wives as they love their own bodies. A man who loves his wife loves himself.
49Eph 5:29 For no one has ever hated his own body, but he nourishes and tenderly cares for it, as the Messiah does the church.
49Eph 5:30 For we are parts of his body - of his flesh and of his bones.
49Eph 5:31 "That is why a man will leave his father and mother and be united with his wife, and the two will become one flesh."
49Eph 5:32 This is a great secret, but I am talking about the Messiah and the church.
49Eph 5:33 But each individual man among you must love his wife as he loves himself; and may the wife fear her husband.532
