621Jn 4:4 Little children, you belong to God and have overcome them, because the one who is in you is greater than the one who is in the world.
621Jn 4:5 These people belong to the world. That is why they speak from the world's perspective, and the world listens to them.
621Jn 4:6 We belong to God. The person who knows God listens to us. Whoever does not belong to God does not listen to us. This is how we know the Spirit of truth and the spirit of deceit.4
621Jn 4:7 Dear friends, let us continually love one another, because love comes from God. Everyone who loves has been born from God and knows God.
621Jn 4:8 The person who does not love does not know God, because God is love.
621Jn 4:9 This is how God's love was revealed among us£º God sent his unique Son into the world so that we might live through him.
621Jn 4:10 This is love£º not that we have loved God, but that he loved us and sent his Son to be the atoning sacrifice for our sins.
621Jn 4:11 Dear friends, if this is the way God loved us, we must also love one another.
621Jn 4:12 No one has ever seen God. If we love one another, God lives in us, and his love is perfected in us.
621Jn 4:13 This is how we know that we abide in him and he in us£º he has given us his Spirit. 
621Jn 4:14 We have seen for ourselves and can testify that the Father has sent his Son to be the Savior of the world.
621Jn 4:15 God abides in the one who acknowledges that Jesus is the Son of God, and he abides in God.
621Jn 4:16 We have come to know and rely on the love that God has for us. God is love, and the person who abides in love abides in God, and God abides in him.
621Jn 4:17 This is how love has been perfected among us£º we will have confidence on the day of judgment because, during our time in this world, we are just like him.
621Jn 4:18 There is no fear where love exists. Rather, perfect love banishes fear, for fear involves punishment, and the person who lives in fear has not been perfected in love. 
621Jn 4:19 We love because God first loved us.
621Jn 4:20 Whoever says, "I love God," but hates his brother is a liar. The one who does not love his brother whom he has seen cannot love the God whom he has not seen.
621Jn 4:21 And this is the commandment that we have from him£º the person who loves God must also love his brother. 
621Jn 5:1 Everyone who believes that Jesus is the Messiah has been born from God, and everyone who loves the parent also loves the child.
621Jn 5:2 This is how we know that we love God's children£º we love God and keep his commandments.
621Jn 5:3 For this demonstrates our love for God£º We keep his commandments, and his commandments are not difficult,
621Jn 5:4 because everyone who is born from God has overcome the world. Our faith is the victory that overcomes the world.
621Jn 5:5 Who overcomes the world? Is it not the person who believes that Jesus is the Son of God - 
621Jn 5:6 This man, Jesus the Messiah, is the one who came by water and blood - not with water only, but with water and with blood. The Spirit is the one who verifies this, because the Spirit is the truth.
621Jn 5:7 For there are three witnesses - 
621Jn 5:8 the Spirit, the water, and the blood - and these three are one.
621Jn 5:9 If we accept human testimony, God's testimony is greater, because it is the testimony of God and because he has testified about his Son.
621Jn 5:10 The person who believes in the Son of God believes this testimony personally. The person who does not believe God has made him a liar by not believing the testimony that he has given about his Son. 
621Jn 5:11 This is the testimony£º God has given us eternal life, and this life is found in his Son.
621Jn 5:12 The person who has the Son has this life. The person who does not have the Son of God does not have this life. 
621Jn 5:13 I have written these things to you who believe in the name of the Son of God so that you may know that you have eternal life.
621Jn 5:14 And this is the confidence that we have in him£º if we ask for anything according to his will, he listens to us.
621Jn 5:15 And if we know that he listens to our requests, we can be sure that we have what we ask him for.
621Jn 5:16 If anyone sees his brother committing a sin that does not lead to death, he should pray that God would give him life. This applies to those who commit sins that do not lead to death. There is a sin that leads to death. I am not telling you to pray about that.
621Jn 5:17 Every kind of wrongdoing is sin, yet there are sins that do not lead to death. 
621Jn 5:18 We know that the person who has been born from God does not go on sinning. Rather, the Son of God protects them, and the evil one cannot harm them.
621Jn 5:19 We know that we are from God and that the whole world lies under the control of the evil one.
621Jn 5:20 We also know that the Son of God has come and has given us understanding so that we may know the true God. We are in union with the one who is true, his Son Jesus the Messiah, who is the true God and eternal life.
621Jn 5:21 Little children, keep yourselves away from idols.
