66Rv 18:6 Do to her as she herself has done, and give her double for her deeds. Mix a double drink for her in the cup she mixed.
66Rv 18:7 Just as she glorified herself and lived in luxury, inflict on her just as much torture and misery. In her heart she says, 'I am a queen on a throne, not a widow. I will never see misery.'
66Rv 18:8 For this reason, her diseases that result in death, misery, and famine will come in a single day. She will be burned up in a fire, because powerful is the Lord God who judges her."
66Rv 18:9 The kings of the earth, who committed sexual immorality with her and lived in luxury with her, will cry and mourn over her when they see the smoke rising from the fire that consumes her.
66Rv 18:10 Frightened by the torture that she experiences, they will stand far away and cry out, "How terrible, how terrible it is for that great city, the powerful city Babylon, because your judgment arrived in a single hour!"
66Rv 18:11 The world's businesses cry and mourn over her, because no one buys their cargo anymore - 
66Rv 18:12 cargo of gold, silver, gems, pearls, fine linen, purple cloth, silk, scarlet cloth, all kinds of scented wood, all articles made of ivory, all articles made of very costly wood, bronze, iron, marble,
66Rv 18:13 cinnamon, spice, incense, myrrh, frankincense, wine, olive oil, flour, wheat, cattle, sheep, horses, chariots, and slaves (that is, human souls) - 
66Rv 18:14 "The fruit that you crafted has abandoned you. All your dainties and your splendor are lost, and no one will ever find them again."
66Rv 18:15 Frightened by the severity of her punishment, businesses that had become rich because of her will stand at a distance, crying and mourning£º
66Rv 18:16 "How terrible, how terrible it is for the great city that was clothed in fine linen, purple, and scarlet and was adorned with gold, gems, and pearls,
66Rv 18:17 because all this wealth has been destroyed in a single hour!" Every ship's captain, everyone who traveled by ship, sailors, and everyone who made a living from the sea stood far away.
66Rv 18:18 When they saw the smoke rising from the fire that consumed her, they began to cry out, "What city was like that great city?"
66Rv 18:19 Then they threw dust on their heads and shouted while crying and mourning£º "How terrible, how terrible it is for the great city, where all who had ships at sea became rich from her wealth, because it has been destroyed in a single hour!
66Rv 18:20 Be happy about her, heaven, saints, apostles, and prophets, for God has condemned her for you!"
66Rv 18:21 Then a powerful angel picked up a stone that was like a large millstone and threw it into the sea, saying, "The great city Babylon will be thrown down violently? and will never be found again.
66Rv 18:22 The sound of harpists, musicians, flutists, and trumpeters will never be heard within you again. No artisan of any trade will ever be found within you again. The sound of a millstone will never be heard within you again.
66Rv 18:23 The light from a lamp will never shine within you again. The voice of a bridegroom and bride will never be heard within you again. For your merchants were the important people of the world, and all the nations were deceived by your witchcraft.
66Rv 18:24 The blood of the world's prophets, saints, and all who had been murdered was found within her."
66Rv 19:1 After these things I heard what sounded like the loud voice of a large crowd in heaven, saying, "Hallelujah! Salvation, glory, and power belong to our God.
66Rv 19:2 His judgments are true and just. He has condemned the notorious prostitute who corrupted the world with her immorality. He has taken revenge on her for the blood of his servants."
66Rv 19:3 A second time they said, "Hallelujah! The smoke goes up from her forever and ever."
66Rv 19:4 The twenty-four elders and the four living creatures bowed down and worshiped God, who was sitting on the throne. They said, "Amen! Hallelujah!"
66Rv 19:5 A voice came from the throne, saying, "Praise our God, all who serve and fear him, from the least important to the most important."
66Rv 19:6 Then I heard what sounded like the voice of a large crowd, like the sound of raging waters, and like the sound of powerful thunderclaps, saying, "Hallelujah! The Lord our God, the Almighty, is reigning.
66Rv 19:7 Let us rejoice, be glad, and give him glory, because the marriage of the lamb has come and his bride has made herself ready.
66Rv 19:8 She has been given the privilege of wearing fine linen, dazzling and pure." (The fine linen represents the righteous deeds of the saints.)
66Rv 19:9 Then the angel said to me, "Write this£º 'How blessed are those who are invited to the marriage supper of the lamb!'" He also told me, "These are the true words of God."
66Rv 19:10 I bowed down at his feet to worship him, but he told me, "Don't do that! I am a fellow servant with you and with your brothers who rely on what Jesus is saying. Worship God, because what Jesus is saying is the spirit of prophecy!" 
66Rv 19:11 Then I saw heaven standing open, and there was a white horse! Its rider is named Faithful and True. He administers justice and wages war righteously.
66Rv 19:12 His eyes are like a flame of fire, and on his head are many royal crowns. He has a name written on him that nobody knows except himself.
66Rv 19:13 He is dressed in a robe dipped in blood, and his name is called the Word of God.
66Rv 19:14 The armies of heaven, wearing fine linen, white and pure, follow him on white horses.
66Rv 19:15 A sharp sword comes out of his mouth to strike down the nations. He will rule them with an iron rod and tread the winepress of the fury of the wrath of God Almighty.
66Rv 19:16 On his robe and his thigh he has a name written£º King of Kings and Lord of Lords
66Rv 19:17 Then I saw an angel standing in the sun. He cried out in a loud voice to all the birds flying overhead, "Come! Gather for the great supper of God.
66Rv 19:18 Eat the flesh of kings, the flesh of commanders, the flesh of warriors, the flesh of horses and their riders, and the flesh of all people, both free and slaves, both unimportant and important."19
66Rv 19:19 Then I saw the beast, the kings of the earth, and their armies gathered to wage war against the rider on the horse and his army.
66Rv 19:20 The beast was captured, along with the false prophet who had performed signs on its behalf. By these signs the false prophet had deceived those who had received the mark of the beast and worshiped its image. Both of them were thrown alive into the lake of fire that burns with sulfur.
66Rv 19:21 The rest were killed by the sword that belonged to the rider on the horse and that came from his mouth, and all the birds gorged themselves with their flesh.
66Rv 20:1 Then I saw an angel coming down from heaven, holding the key to the bottomless pit, with a large chain in his hand.
66Rv 20:2 He captured the dragon, that ancient serpent, also known as the devil and Satan, and tied him up for a thousand years.
66Rv 20:3 He threw him into the bottomless pit, locked it, and sealed it over him to keep him from deceiving the nations anymore until the thousand years were over. After that he must be set free for a little while. 
66Rv 20:4 Then I saw thrones, and those who sat on them were given authority to judge. I also saw the souls of those who had been beheaded because of their testimony about Jesus and because of the word of God. They had not worshiped the beast or its image and had not received its mark on their foreheads or hands. They came back to life and ruled with the Messiah for a thousand years.
66Rv 20:5 The rest of the dead did not come back to life until the thousand years were over. This is the first resurrection.
66Rv 20:6 How blessed and holy are those who participate in the first resurrection! The second death has no power over them. They will be priests of God and the Messiah, and will rule with him for a thousand years. 
66Rv 20:7 When the thousand years are over, Satan will be freed from his prison.
66Rv 20:8 He will go out to deceive Gog and Magog, the nations at the four corners of the earth, and gather them for war. They are as numerous as the sands of the seashore.
66Rv 20:9 They marched over the broad expanse of the earth and surrounded the camp of the saints and the beloved city. Fire came from God out of heaven and burned them up,
66Rv 20:10 and the devil who deceived them was thrown into the lake of fire and sulfur, where the beast and the false prophet were. They will be tortured day and night forever and ever. 
66Rv 20:11 Then I saw a large, white throne and the one who was sitting on it. The earth and the heavens fled from his presence, and no place was found for them.
66Rv 20:12 I saw the dead, both unimportant and important, standing in front of the throne, and books were open. Another book was opened - the Book of Life. The dead were judged according to their actions, as recorded in the books.
66Rv 20:13 The sea gave up the dead that were in it, and Death and Hades gave up the dead that were in them, and all were judged according to their actions.
66Rv 20:14 Death and Hades were thrown into the lake of fire. (This is the second death - the lake of fire.)
66Rv 20:15 Anyone whose name was not found written in the Book of Life was thrown into the lake of fire. 
66Rv 21:1 Then I saw a new heaven and a new earth, because the first heaven and the first earth had disappeared, and the sea was gone.
66Rv 21:2 I also saw the holy city, New Jerusalem, coming down from God out of heaven, prepared like a bride adorned for her husband.
66Rv 21:3 I heard a loud voice from the throne say, "See, the tabernacle of God is among humans! He will make his home with them, and they will be his people. God himself will be with them, and he will be their God.
66Rv 21:4 He will wipe every tear from their eyes. There won't be death anymore. There won't be any grief, crying, or pain, because the first things have disappeared." 
66Rv 21:5 The one sitting on the throne said, "See, I am making all things new!"He said, "Write this£º 'These words are trustworthy and true.'" 
66Rv 21:6 Then he said to me, "It has happened! I am the Alpha and the Omega, the beginning and the end. I will freely give a drink from the spring of the water of life to the one who is thirsty.
66Rv 21:7 The person who conquers will inherit these things. I will be his God, and he will be my son.
66Rv 21:8 But people who are cowardly, unfaithful, detestable, murderers, sexually immoral, sorcerers, idolaters, and all liars will find themselves in the lake that burns with fire and sulfur. This is the second death." 
66Rv 21:9 Then one of the seven angels who had the seven bowls full of the seven last plagues came to me and said, "Come! I will show you the bride, the wife of the lamb."
66Rv 21:10 He carried me away in the Spirit to a large, high mountain and showed me the holy city, Jerusalem, coming down from God out of heaven.
66Rv 21:11 The glory of God was its radiance, and its light was like a valuable gem, like jasper, as clear as crystal.
66Rv 21:12 It had a large, high wall with twelve gates. Twelve angels were at the gates, and the names of the twelve tribes of Israel were written on the gates.
66Rv 21:13 There were three gates on the east, three gates on the north, three gates on the south, and three gates on the west.
66Rv 21:14 The wall of the city had twelve foundations, and the twelve names of the twelve apostles of the lamb were written on them.21
66Rv 21:15 The angel who was talking to me had a gold measuring rod to measure the city, its gates, and its walls.
66Rv 21:16 The city was square£º its length was the same as its width. He measured the city with his rod, and it was about1 ,374 miles long. Its length, width, and height were the same.
66Rv 21:17 He also measured its wall. According to the human measurement that the angel was using, it was 242 feet.
66Rv 21:18 Its wall was made of jasper. The city was made of pure gold, as clear as glass.
66Rv 21:19 The foundations of the city wall were decorated with all kinds of gems£º The first foundation was jasper, the second sapphire, the third agate, the fourth emerald,
66Rv 21:20 the fifth onyx, the sixth carnelian, the seventh chrysolite, the eighth beryl, the ninth topaz, the tenth chrysoprase, the eleventh jacinth, and the twelfth amethyst.
66Rv 21:21 The twelve gates were twelve pearls, and each gate was made of a single pearl. The street of the city was made of pure gold, as clear as glass. 
66Rv 21:22 I saw no temple in it, because the Lord God Almighty and the lamb are its temple.
66Rv 21:23 The city doesn't need any sun or moon to give it light, because the glory of God gave it light, and the lamb was its lamp.
66Rv 21:24 The nations will walk in its light, and the kings of the earth will bring their glory into it.
66Rv 21:25 Its gates will never be shut at the end of the day - because there will be no night there.
66Rv 21:26 People will bring the glory and wealth of the nations into it.
66Rv 21:27 Nothing unclean, or anyone who does anything detestable, and no one who tells lies will ever enter it. Only those whose names are written in the lamb's Book of Life will enter it.
66Rv 22:1 Then the angel showed me the river of the water of life, as clear as crystal. It was flowing from the throne of God and the lamb.
66Rv 22:2 Between the city street and the river, the tree of life was visible from each side. It produced twelve kinds of fruit, each month having its own fruit. The leaves of the tree are for the healing of the nations.
66Rv 22:3 There will no longer be any curse. The throne of God and the lamb will be in the city. His servants will worship him
66Rv 22:4 and see his face, and his name will be on their foreheads.
66Rv 22:5 There will be no more night, and they will not need any light from lamps or the sun because the Lord God will shine on them. They will rule forever and ever. 
66Rv 22:6 He said to me, "These words are trustworthy and true. The Lord God of the spirits and of the prophets has sent his messenger to show his servants the things that must happen soon." 
66Rv 22:7 "See! I am coming soon! How blessed is the person who keeps the words of the prophecy in this book!" 
66Rv 22:8 I, John, heard and saw these things. When I had heard and seen them, I bowed down to worship at the feet of the angel who had been showing me these things.
66Rv 22:9 But he told me, "Don't do that! I am a fellow servant with you, your brothers the prophets, and those who keep the words in this book. Worship God!" 
66Rv 22:10 Then he said to me, "Don't seal up the words of the prophecy in this book, because the time is near.
66Rv 22:11 Let the one who does what is evil continue to do evil, and let the filthy person continue to be filthy, and the righteous person continue to do what is right, and the holy person continue to be holy." 
66Rv 22:12 "See! I am coming soon! My reward is with me to repay everyone according to his action.
66Rv 22:13 I am the Alpha and the Omega, the first and the last, the beginning and the end.
66Rv 22:14 "How blessed are those who wash their robes so that they may have the right to the tree of life and may go through the gates into the city!
66Rv 22:15 Outside are dogs, sorcerers, immoral people, murderers, idolaters, and everyone who loves and practices falsehood.
66Rv 22:16 "I, Jesus, have sent my angel to give this testimony to you for the churches. I am the root and descendent of David, the bright morning star."
66Rv 22:17 The Spirit and the bride say, "Come!" Let everyone who hears this say, "Come!" Let everyone who is thirsty come! Let anyone who wants the water of life take it as a gift!
66Rv 22:18 I warn everyone who hears the words of the prophecy in this book£º If anyone adds anything to them, God will strike him with the plagues that are written in this book.
66Rv 22:19 If anyone takes away any words from the book of this prophecy, God will take away his portion of the tree of life and the holy city that are described in this book.
66Rv 22:20 The one who is testifying to these things says, "Yes, I am coming soon!" Amen! Come, Lord Jesus!
66Rv 22:21 May the grace of the Lord Jesus be with all the saints. Amen.
